<br>
That puts my wis at 202 or 199 with ES arms. I know I will lose wis with resist stuff but thats ok. SVM SVC and SVF are what I need to get higher. Thanks for any help <p>Baking: 153 (DIE Brownie!)
Brewing: 150
Tailoring: 87 (I'm working on it. DIE Cat! DIE Spider!)
Nuppin 46 druid of CoP</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unuppin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nuppin</A> at: 9/20/01 6:04:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquigsby.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quigsby</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/19/01 3:52:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist gear for PoH PoF and Vox</span><hr size=1> First piece I'll reccomend is a Crown of the Froglok Kings.  I wear it as my every day helm.  +20 CR/FR<br>
<br>
perfect.<br>
 <br>
<br>
Besides that you have Velium/Plat Diamond resist rings.<br>
<br>
Later on you'll be shooting for Blue Diamond resist gear.  I reccomend getting earrings first, then choker, followed by Tiara (for MR), and then bracers if you don't have verm yet.<br>
<br>
In PoF you'll get Verm arms which have +7 SVMagic, which is very nice.  And I believe Verm Bracers give +7 CR/FR.<br>
<br>
Other stuffs you can do are the Velious Kromrif Legs/Coldain Military Wristgaurd quests - looks em up ;)  They have mild resist (+5 to two resists in both cases). <p><font color="#006600"><font size=+2>Quigsby Quickfoot</font></font>
