"Thought this be madness, yet there is method in't."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upeoni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peoni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/20/01 3:05:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist gear for PoH PoF and Vox</span><hr size=1> See if you can join a group in Chardok, Killing mobs around the entrance/exit will eventually get a sarnak battleshied to drop (10MR/FR/CR +great stats)<br>
<br>
Lower Guk<br>
----------<br>
As the above poster said, try for a froglok crown (20FR/CR), <br>
<br>
While your at the king spawn, try and keep clearing the noble spawn (not too far away) for a -:<br>
<br>
While gold necklace (7FR/CR/MR)<br>
<br>
Droga<br>
------<br>
Shroud of nature (6wis 8FR/CR) is easily obtainable from Droga with a group <br>
<br>
And while your in Droga, why not take a trip down to the soothsayer and get an -:<br>
<br>
Earring of essence (30hp 10MR)<br>
<br>
Jeweller<br>
--------<br>
Velium Diamond Rings (8vs all) - made my a jeweller<br>
Gold Diamond Mask (10FR/CR 5PR/DR 3MR) - made by jeweller<br>
other blue diamond items are very nice (earrings/bracers) but BD's aren't too common, and even a max skill jeweller will still fail alot on bracers...<br>
<br>
Lake of ill omen<br>
---------------<br>
Woven legs (10fr), mantle (5cr) drop at sarnak fort<br>
<br>
Permafrost<br>
-----------<br>
Cloak of the Ice bear (20cr) - for vox is a must<br>
<br>
Najena<br>
-------<br>
Hollowed bone bracers (7mr)<br>
<br>
<br>
These items will probably cut into your wisdom quite a bit, all however are droppable so you can buy/trade for any (most are fairly cheap too), plus you can also get an enchanter wis buff on the raid...<br>
One thing to remember tho - if you Die with lots of mana left because the AE took you out - you've not served your purpose on the raid, and spending all the raid fearred because you're MR was too low, is no fun at all...<br>
I'd recommend at minimum you try for 70MR/100FR or CR against vox or nagafen (unbuffed) and then get enchanter group MR+ your own FR/CR buffs. Try and get more MR if possible to help resist the fear effects.<br>
<br>
Also Vox/Nagafen AE's remove your 1 buff every time they use their breath weapon (starting at the top and working down), one way to combat this is to use an instant click item every time they breath - i.e. they dispel your first buff, you rebuff instantly (rinse/repeat) - as these fights are indoors you can't rely on Jboots to help here. The cheapest option you'll have is the tinkered made telescope (although use it a bit before the raid as its kinda disorientating at first)<br>
<br>
Also remember, you're there to heal not nuke - the resist rate on your nukes will be too much and the mobs are 100% mr (so your MR dots won't land), save your mana to keep people alive and in doing so they'll get to do the damage on your behalf. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uellendilhsilvermist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellendilh Silvermist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/20/01 5:09:50 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~phiphix/nfalogo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist gear for PoH PoF and Vox</span><hr size=1> POH - you don't need any specific resist gear there. Go with Wis/AC/mana/hp items as usual.<br>
<br>
POF - same as above, unless you pull ;-)<br>
<br>
Vox - go with CR/MR as much as possible. Don't hesitate to sacrifice wis/ac. If you are feared or dead, a full bar of mana will not help you. <p><p><HR>
